de.mrapp.android.adapter

Interface Filter<DataType>

  • Type Parameters:
    DataType - The type of the instances, which should be filtered
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    GroupFilter

    public interface Filter<DataType>
extends java.io.Serializable
    Defines the interface, a class, which should allow to filter instances of a specific type by using a regular expression, must implement.
    Since:
    0.1.0
    Author:
    Michael Rapp

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      boolean match(DataType data, java.lang.String query, int flags)
      Returns, whether a specific instance does match a regular expression, or not.

    • Method Detail

      • match

        boolean match(@NonNull
              DataType data,
              @NonNull
              java.lang.String query,
              int flags)
        Returns, whether a specific instance does match a regular expression, or not.
        Parameters:
        data - The instance, which should be filtered, as an instance of the generic type DataType. The instance may not be null
        query - The query, which should be used for filtering, as a String. The query may not be null
        flags - The flags, which should be used for filtering, as an Integer value or 0, if no flags should be used
        Returns:
        True, if the instance does match the given regular expression, false otherwise
